3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEXC calculates TON/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC, using a time-weighted average premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange applies a base rate of 0.01% with premium adjustments based on market conditions. Zero maker fees on MEXC create asymmetric cost advantages for arbitrageurs managing funding rate positions through the 8-hour cycles."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TON","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's growing DeFi ecosystem and Telegram integration create predictable funding rate spikes during major announcements or network upgrades. The pair benefits from MEXC's aggressive listing strategy, often featuring TON perpetuals before other major exchanges, creating temporary funding rate premiums worth capturing."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON/USDT funding rates on MEXC typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% during normal market conditions, with extreme rates reaching +0.5% during major ecosystem announcements. The token shows strong correlation with broader layer-1 sentiment, particularly during DeFi season rallies. Weekend funding rates tend to normalize due to reduced institutional activity, while weekday rates often spike during Asian trading hours when Telegram-related news typically breaks. Historical data shows consistent positive funding bias during TON network upgrade cycles and major partnership announcements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEXC's zero maker fees create profitable arbitrage windows even with modest funding rate differentials of 0.02-0.03% per cycle. The exchange's thinner order books for TON require careful position sizing, typically limiting arbitrage positions to $50k-100k to avoid significant slippage. Cross-exchange arbitrage works best pairing MEXC with Binance or OKX during high volatility periods when funding rate spreads widen beyond 0.1%. The 8-hour funding cycle allows for three daily capture opportunities, making consistent small profits more viable than hunting for extreme rate events."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's relatively lower liquidity on MEXC compared to major tokens creates elevated liquidation risks during flash crashes, requiring conservative leverage usage below 5x for funding rate strategies. The exchange's questionable volume reporting means order book depth analysis requires extra scrutiny before executing large positions. Regulatory uncertainties around MEXC operations pose counterparty risks that should be factored into position sizing decisions. Weekend funding rate reversals can occur rapidly due to reduced market maker presence, making stop-loss discipline essential for overnight positions."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does MEXC's zero maker fee affect TON funding rate arbitrage profitability?","answer":"Zero maker fees eliminate a significant cost component, making arbitrage profitable at funding rate differentials as low as 0.02% per 8-hour cycle. This fee advantage allows for more frequent trading and smaller profit margins while maintaining overall profitability compared to exchanges charging 0.02-0.05% maker fees."},{"question":"What are the optimal position sizes for TON/USDT funding arbitrage on MEXC?","answer":"Given TON's order book depth on MEXC, positions should typically stay below $100k to avoid significant slippage. During high volatility periods, reducing position sizes to $25k-50k helps maintain execution quality while still capturing meaningful funding rate differentials."},{"question":"How do TON ecosystem events impact funding rates on MEXC?","answer":"Major TON network upgrades, Telegram integration announcements, and DeFi protocol launches typically drive funding rates positive by 0.1-0.3% above baseline. These events create 24-48 hour windows of elevated rates, though they also increase price volatility risks."},{"question":"What are the key differences between TON funding rates on MEXC versus other exchanges?","answer":"MEXC often shows 0.05-0.15% higher funding rates than Binance or OKX during bullish TON periods due to retail-heavy user base and aggressive long positioning. However, this premium can reverse quickly during market stress when MEXC's thinner liquidity creates wider bid-ask spreads."}]}]
